NgModule is the root module for angular
Module file uses @NgModule annotation to declare a module
Need to import this for module declare: import { NgModule } from '@angular/core'

Component to define a view with template
@Component, needs to import {Component} from '@angular/core'
A component with:
  - selector: - css selector
  - template :``, or templateUrl:'./xx.html'
  - styleUrls:['./xx.css','./xxx.css']


Angular cli:
 ng new project_name
 ng serve --open //run under the project path
 
 Syntax:
 {{var}} - binding wiht double curly braces
 [(ngModule)]='var'  - two way binding, you should import FormsModule form @angular/forms
 [class.myclass]='condition' - control the css class
 @Input() var;  - import {input} from @angular/core, property binding: [var]="xx"
 @Injectable - declare service import {Injectable} from @angluar/core
 
 
 lifecycle hooking of angular:
 ngOnInit
 
 
 
 pipes in angular (pipe can be used to transform and format the string shown in html)
 - uppercase - format string to uppercase, eg {{name | uppercase}}, this will be shown in uppercase of name
 - date - format date, eg, currentDate = new Date(), {{currentDate | date}}, pipe with parameter following by a colon 



